00:32:05,299 --> 00:32:07,554
I love you.
You are the life that I wanted.

509
00:32:07,679 --> 00:32:09,879
Then let's "have" that life.

510
00:32:11,485 --> 00:32:12,805
We can have that life.

511
00:32:12,973 --> 00:32:14,431
You didn't want to give up hope.

512
00:32:14,904 --> 00:32:15,954
Then don't.

513
00:32:17,070 --> 00:32:19,603
We have two conflicting visions.
We can choose...

514
00:32:19,771 --> 00:32:21,564
which one we wanna believe in.

515
00:32:25,276 --> 00:32:26,476
I choose hope.

516
00:32:29,132 --> 00:32:30,136
You're right.

517
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:47,663
Thanks for coming out.

518
00:32:47,788 --> 00:32:50,455
- Is everything all right, sir?
- Everything's fine.

519
00:32:52,827 --> 00:32:54,594
That's why I called you out,
actually.

520
00:32:55,195 --> 00:32:57,384
I thought you might be
upset with me, for...

521
00:32:57,918 --> 00:32:59,459
telling you what I told you.

522
00:33:03,570 --> 00:33:05,520
I've spent the last few weeks

523
00:33:06,804 --> 00:33:08,569
tortured by what I saw,

524
00:33:09,326 --> 00:33:11,326
up and down, living in limbo.

525
00:33:11,865 --> 00:33:14,243
But your story, what you told me...

526
00:33:16,020 --> 00:33:17,845
You've finally given me some peace.

527
00:33:18,444 --> 00:33:21,290
And I was hoping
maybe I could return the favor.

528
00:33:31,468 --> 00:33:34,011
You won't be the first screwed up vet
this place has hired.

529
00:33:34,944 --> 00:33:35,888
Thank you.

530
00:33:36,787 --> 00:33:38,306
No, thank you.

531
00:33:42,996 --> 00:33:45,189
You're a real artist.
You could totally sell these.

532
00:33:46,393 --> 00:33:47,393
Thanks.

533
00:33:48,052 --> 00:33:51,002
I'd give 'em away for nothing
if somebody could help me find her.

534
00:33:51,127 --> 00:33:52,127
Thanks.

535
00:33:52,864 --> 00:33:55,105
You don't remember her name
or where she lives?

536
00:33:55,230 --> 00:33:57,167
Just, I remember the images...

537
00:33:57,292 --> 00:33:59,109
But I just can't put them together.

538
00:33:59,326 --> 00:34:00,871
You remember how you felt about her?

539
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:07,211
- You have to find her, Bryce.
- How? She could be anywhere.

540
00:34:07,379 --> 00:34:10,589
Look at your paintings. Look at her.
It's Japan. It has to be.

541
00:34:10,757 --> 00:34:13,300
Do you have any idea
how many people live in Japan?

542
00:34:13,468 --> 00:34:15,010
Put your story up on Mosaic.

543
00:34:15,327 --> 00:34:18,313
Even if she doesn't see it, someone
she knows might. It's worth a shot.

544
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:52,850
- Morning, guys.
- Morning.

545
00:34:52,975 --> 00:34:55,633
- You coming to the meeting?
- You two go ahead. Demetri?

546
00:34:56,286 --> 00:34:59,722
I left something on your desk. Can you
make sure it gets into the right hands?

547
00:35:01,319 --> 00:35:02,347
See you later.

548
00:35:10,021 --> 00:35:12,276
We've got this Raynaud guy
in custody.

549
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:13,444
Now what?

550
00:35:13,767 --> 00:35:16,937
He's still refusing to name names,
give us an idea of who's in charge.

551
00:35:17,062 --> 00:35:20,148
My sense is
this people aren't killers...

552
00:35:20,273 --> 00:35:21,285
Just lost,

553
00:35:21,453 --> 00:35:22,796
aggressive nihilists.

554
00:35:22,921 --> 00:35:25,150
Your sense?
You've gotta do better than that.

555
00:35:25,275 --> 00:35:28,167
You can break any perp.
You've just gotta change your approach.

556
00:35:28,832 --> 00:35:30,012
Raynaud's different.

557
00:35:30,670 --> 00:35:32,129
Can't threaten him with anything.

558
00:35:33,146 --> 00:35:34,631
He's got nothing to lose.

559
00:35:35,586 --> 00:35:37,551
He has seen his future,

560
00:35:37,719 --> 00:35:39,303
and it is bleak.

561
00:35:39,769 --> 00:35:42,222
He doesn't even know
how it's gonna happen. It could be...

562
00:35:43,143 --> 00:35:44,475
a fall, a fight,

563
00:35:44,643 --> 00:35:47,311
a shooting, a car accident.
The possibilities are infinite.

564
00:35:49,522 --> 00:35:52,319
The guy's walking on eggshells
every minute of the day,

565
00:35:53,068 --> 00:35:54,610
just waiting for the hammer to drop.

566
00:35:57,033 --> 00:35:59,531
<i>Al, I just got off the phone
with hospital.</i>

567
00:36:00,961 --> 00:36:03,258
<i>They took her off life support
an hour ago.</i>

568
00:36:03,383 --> 00:36:04,414
<i>I'm sorry, Al.</i>

569
00:36:04,539 --> 00:36:05,589
<i>She's gone.</i>

570
00:36:07,663 --> 00:36:10,042
Every day, he wakes up wondering
if today is the day...

571
00:36:11,007 --> 00:36:14,129
If today is the day his future's
finally gonna catch up with him.

572
00:36:15,347 --> 00:36:17,023
What's gonna happen to her children?

573
00:36:17,148 --> 00:36:20,052
<i>It looks like the kids will have
to be placed in foster care.</i>

574
00:36:21,190 --> 00:36:23,238
Those two boys are orphans...

575
00:36:24,981 --> 00:36:25,933
Because of me?

576
00:36:26,573 --> 00:36:28,894
<i>No, Celia's death
was an accident, okay?</i>

577
00:36:29,063 --> 00:36:31,188
- <i>It could've happened to anyone.</i>
- But it didn't.

578
00:36:32,334 --> 00:36:33,357
It was my fault.

579
00:36:36,684 --> 00:36:37,834
I killed her.

580
00:36:40,466 --> 00:36:42,950
- The change in...
- Stop. Stop!

581
00:37:05,736 --> 00:37:07,015
Al! Talk to us!

582
00:37:07,657 --> 00:37:08,818
Just talk to us.

583
00:37:08,943 --> 00:37:10,227
We can fix this.

584
00:37:10,395 --> 00:37:13,073
We can find her. We can find Celia.
We can protect her.

585
00:37:13,198 --> 00:37:15,941
Anything you need,
we can find a way to make it happen.

586
00:37:16,109 --> 00:37:19,278
- Come on, Al.
- It can happen anytime, anywhere.

587
00:37:20,433 --> 00:37:23,030
- I don't even know how it happens.
- Al, listen to me.

588
00:37:23,409 --> 00:37:25,909
You're alive six months from now.
You saw it.

589
00:37:26,077 --> 00:37:27,494
Man, you saw it!

590
00:37:27,894 --> 00:37:29,310
But if I'm not here...

591
00:37:29,435 --> 00:37:31,290
- Come on, get down.
- If I'm not here...

592
00:37:34,322 --> 00:37:37,296
- It means we can change things.
- Al, please get down.

593
00:37:37,464 --> 00:37:38,422
What I saw...

594
00:37:39,462 --> 00:37:40,549
I killed her.

595
00:37:41,358 --> 00:37:42,342
What you saw...

596
00:37:44,662 --> 00:37:46,553
doesn't have to play out that way.

597
00:37:47,265 --> 00:37:48,808
What are you talking about?

598
00:37:49,380 --> 00:37:51,321
I found a way to change the game.

599
00:37:53,896 --> 00:37:56,565
<i>Al, listen to me.
Celia's death was an accident.</i>

600
00:37:57,395 --> 00:37:59,427
<i>A terrible, random accident.</i>

601
00:38:00,403 --> 00:38:03,121
<i>There's nothing
you could've done to avoid this.</i>

602
00:39:11,806 --> 00:39:12,906
<i>"Dear Celia,</i>

603
00:39:14,470 --> 00:39:16,133
<i>"I don't know your last name,</i>

604
00:39:16,258 --> 00:39:18,198
<i>"and I don't know where you live,</i>

605
00:39:18,323 --> 00:39:20,486
<i>"but I know
you have two young boys...</i>

606
00:39:21,860 --> 00:39:23,260
<i>"Twins, I believe.</i>

607
00:39:25,396 --> 00:39:27,596
<i>"And I know
you didn't have a flash-forward.</i>

608
00:39:29,361 --> 00:39:31,430
<i>"I understand how terrifying that is</i>

609
00:39:32,735 --> 00:39:34,740
<i>"and how powerless
you must be feeling.</i>

610
00:39:37,441 --> 00:39:39,091
<i>"But I want you to know</i>

611
00:39:39,752 --> 00:39:41,402
<i>"that you are not alone</i>

612
00:39:42,946 --> 00:39:44,646
<i>"and that your situation</i>

613
00:39:45,182 --> 00:39:47,281
<i>"is not as hopeless as you think.</i>

614
00:39:50,215 --> 00:39:52,619
<i>"Our paths were meant to cross,</i>

615
00:39:54,337 --> 00:39:55,475
<i>"I didn't know how.</i>

616
00:39:56,834 --> 00:39:58,334
<i>"I didn't know when.</i>

617
00:40:01,314 --> 00:40:02,904
<i>"But things have changed now.</i>

618
00:40:04,325 --> 00:40:07,119
<i>"Things are no longer going to unfold
as I had feared.</i>

619
00:40:10,114 --> 00:40:11,663
<i>"My gift to you</i>

620
00:40:12,301 --> 00:40:14,301
<i>"is release from that dread...</i>

621
00:40:18,228 --> 00:40:21,084
<i>"From the feeling
that you're no longer in control.</i>

622
00:40:33,848 --> 00:40:35,139
<i>"We will never meet.</i>

623
00:40:37,035 --> 00:40:38,614
<i>"I will never know you.</i>

624
00:40:39,705 --> 00:40:41,155
<i>"So live your life.</i>

625
00:40:42,734 --> 00:40:44,232
<i>"Live every day.</i>

626
00:40:46,584 --> 00:40:49,846
<i>"And know that the future
is unwritten.</i>

627
00:40:53,429 --> 00:40:54,833
<i>"Make the most of that."</i>

628
